title: Faster With Newbern and Cotten
subTitle: David Newbern and Mike Cotten use their knowledge and resources to transform cars and make them better, faster and stronger on a budget.

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: The girls do a top-end rebuild, install an EFI, and put the factory side exhaust back on a 1969 Corvette.

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: The owner of a 2018 Kia Stinger GT wants some aftermarket goodies installed; the crew makes this beast into a monster with upgraded exhaust, a new cold-air intake and a couple of other surprises.

title: Salvage Hunters: Classic Cars
subTitle: Drew and Paul rescue a classic: a Vauxhall Viva. The car was extensively modified in the 1960s but after years in storage, it's well past its best.

title: Wheeler Dealers
subTitle: Sold as the world's first sporty luxury car, the Thunderbird sold healthily in its day. Mike is searching for a 57' edition that can make him a profit.

title: Bad Chad Customs
subTitle: In rural Canning, Nova Scotia, Chad Hiltz runs a modest auto body shop with a legendary reputation. A custom car artist and master builder, 'Bad Chad' and his tight-knit team can turn metal from the junkyards into award-winning cars.

title: Street Outlaws
subTitle: Farmtruck and AZN invite all the 405 racers out to Willow Springs for a competition. The racers must pair up and the fastest combined times will take home $10,000.

title: Faster With Newbern and Cotten

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: A 1971 Oldsmobile Cutlass has a few issues with leaks and power loss. The crew tracks down the problems, and then converts the transmission from automatic to manual so the owner can drive a classic as it was meant to be enjoyed.

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: A 2003 BMW 325i needs a new timing chain and has a parasitic electrical draw; each of these issues requires special tools to fix, but they're nothing the team can't handle.

title: Salvage Hunters: Classic Cars

title: Wheeler Dealers

title: Street Outlaws
subTitle: The 405 is in California taking on Boddie and his group of racers, but it has not been an easy night so far. This time around, there is more than just money on the line.

title: Fastest Cars in the Dirty South
subTitle: Eric Malone confronts Team 256 about last year's race against the Memphis 10 that divided the team. Plus, Eric rallies his remaining team for a shout-out to defend their title.

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: A '69 Mustang with a supercharged stroker engine is in need of more throttle response, so the team bolts on a new EFI system; once that's mounted and a new fuel pump is installed, there is no hiding the extra boost.

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: The girls find a stock AMG E 55 and do some European hot rodding; to get the AMG ready to roll, they put on a smaller pulley to get the supercharger to spin faster, bolt on some long tube headers, and load in a tune.
